OL,5, Pressure is growing on BBC chairman    
OL,6, Richard Sharp to resign amid the Gary  
OL,7, Lineker impartiality row.              
OL,9,FLiberal Democrat leader Sir Ed Davey   
OL,10,Fsaid the presenter's suspension "has   
OL,11,Fshown failure at the top".             
OL,13,FMr Sharp's appointment is being        
OL,14,Finvestigated over his relationship with
OL,15,FBoris Johnson. He denies wrongdoing.   
OL,17,FBut ex-BBC head Greg Dyke said the     
OL,18,FSharp allegations had "helped fuel the 
OL,19,Fperception" the corporation bowed to   
OL,20,Fgovernment pressure on Lineker.        
